## 2. Enterprise Edition (Commercial License)

The source code located in the `/ee` (Enterprise Edition) directory is **PROPRIETARY SOFTWARE**.

- These files are **NOT** open source.
- They are **NOT** covered by the MIT License.
- Usage, copying, modification, or distribution of these files requires a valid **Commercial License Agreement**.

Unauthorized use of the `/ee` directory contents is strictly prohibited. To obtain a commercial license, please contact us at [your-email@example.com] or visit [your-website.com].

